  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It is terribly important for people to realize that [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] they Jews were pinned in and pitted against such immense powers that there was no possibility [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] to know what to do, and certainly there was no possibility for any really meaningful defense or resistance.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] This is, by and large, true of all of Central and Eastern European Jewry, but it is, I would say, with much greater force true of Hungary.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It is 1944, and the collapse of Germany was reasonably certain by that time, and certainly could be expected.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I certainly was convinced that the war couldn't go on for much longer, and I-- you know, we know from history that most of the allies also saw, so to say, the-- the end of the war, foresaw the victory.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But Hungary was locked in.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was, for years, no border of Hungary that was not occupied by Germany, or that was free of German-supported and-- and German-guided domestic Nazis.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there was no way in which you could organize, obtain the means of-- of defense or armament.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] There was no escape route, really.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "At one time, the remaining Jews came to Hungary because it seemed to have been a little better there, and then, after the Romania [INAUDIBLE] war, some of Hungarian Jews ran to Hung-- to Romania.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But there was no-- no outlet.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was no border.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There were no-- no means of communication.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had what probably was as good knowledge as could be had before the-- before [INAUDIBLE] and the Slovakian Jews became aware of all the actual details of the Auschwitz annihilation process, which was somewhat later than-- than we were deported already.",
      "word_count": 42
    }
  ],
